  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Coosoproda vers une coop&#xE9;rative professionnelle</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Achat de 2 balance plate-formeAchat de 1 Humidim&#xE8;tre &#xE0; grain &#xC9;coles champs paysan et pratique de la Gestion Integr&#xE9;e de la Fertilit&#xE9; des Sols (GIFS)S&#xE9;ances d&apos;information des membres du contrat riz et campagnes de mobilisation des non-membres &#xE0; rejoindre la cooperative. R&#xE9;vision du MAPAF (manuel de procedures administratives et financi&#xE8;res) Achat d&apos;un modem pour acces internet  frais mensuel de communication et papeterie bureauAtelier pour le d&#xE9;veloppement d&apos;un plan strat&#xE9;gique (plan financier inclus)Atelier pour le d&#xE9;veloppement d&apos;un plan d&apos;affaire (+plan de tr&#xE9;sorerie et plan des operations)Am&#xE9;lioration de la comptabilit&#xE9; en Excel et pr&#xE9;paration des &#xE9;tats financiersSuivi du contrat et des livraisons &#xE0; Bralima</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Established in December 2008  the cooperative of solidarity for the production of agricultural products (COSOOPRODA) is a cooperative of farmers of Luberizi structured in the first degree  with a membership of 316 members having released each one its expenses of adhesion. It develops several products and services for its members  including: paddy production and processing in white rice  sale of fertilizer for soil fertilization  agricultural mechanization  storage of rice members and non-members.About the commercial activities  COSOOPRODA currently reaches a capital of approximately 101 000 US dollars thanks to the support and the own efforts of the cooperative including the investments. This situation gives it a good position and assets to evolve properly.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The cooperative would like to  professionalize in the activity of collecting and selling rice of its members  in order to make it more profitable. So  they can earn more income and sell large quantities of quality rice to the Bralima.</narrative>
  </description>
